# PART 3 \'97 DOCUMENT INGESTION SYSTEM\
\
## Ingestion goals\
Build a durable ingestion pipeline that:\
- accepts uploads from existing UI\
- supports native-text PDFs and scanned PDFs\
- stores original files unchanged\
- generates processed page images\
- extracts OCR/HTR\
- classifies page types\
- extracts structured maintenance events\
- indexes searchable text and metadata\
- writes review tasks when confidence is weak\
- updates document status progressively\
- notifies frontend in real time or via polling-compatible status changes\
\
## Required pipeline stages\
1. upload intake\
2. file validation\
3. virus / safety checks where practical\
4. page splitting / rasterization\
5. image preprocessing\
6. orientation correction\
7. document/page classification\
8. OCR / HTR\
9. structured extraction\
10. confidence scoring\
11. indexing\
12. review queue generation\
13. aircraft summary / timeline update\
14. reminder / AD recompute triggers\
\
## Page preprocessing requirements\
Handle:\
- deskew\
- rotate\
- split double-page spreads if needed\
- denoise\
- contrast enhancement\
- adaptive thresholding where useful\
- margin crop\
- blank page / backside detection\
- attachment and insert detection\
\
## Page types\
At minimum classify:\
- cover\
- engine log\
- prop log\
- airframe log\
- avionics log\
- maintenance record page\
- inspection entry\
- annual inspection\
- 100-hour inspection\
- AD compliance page\
- FAA Form 337\
- FAA Form 8130-3\
- work order\
- yellow tag / serviceable tag\
- status sheet\
- weight and balance\
- STC / manual / reference\
- blank / ignore\
- unknown-needs-review\
\
## OCR / HTR strategy\
Use a confidence-aware ensemble approach:\
- primary pass: Google Document AI\
- fallback or comparison: AWS Textract\
- if confidence remains weak or handwriting is ambiguous, use OpenAI vision-based extraction reasoning on page image + neighboring page context\
\
Do not silently merge low-confidence text into truth.\
Every extracted field must carry confidence.\
Low-confidence fields/pages must generate review tasks.\
\
## Confidence policy\
- 90\'96100: auto-accept\
- 70\'9689: accept with caution flag\
- 50\'9669: review queue\
- 0\'9649: do not treat as canonical; review required\
